# design discussion:

- 
% What properties does this design provide? Three core properties are provided.
% First, processing engines remain stateless regarding message storage, allowing
% crash recovery through mailbox replay. Second, the separation enables
% independent scaling of message ingestion (via mailbox distribution) and
% processing logic. Third, the pull-based mechanism implements automatic
% backpressure ---mailboxes naturally throttle message flow when processing engines
% become overloaded.


% \begin{remark}[Idempotency]
% The $\mathsf{append}$ operation is designed to be idempotent to support
% reliable message delivery. Duplicate $\mathsf{append}$ messages from network
% retries are safely absorbed by the mailbox's state management.
% \end{remark}

% \begin{remark}[Persistence]
% While not required by the definition, practical implementations typically make
% mailbox engines persistent through write-ahead logging or snapshotting to
% prevent message loss during failures.
% \end{remark}